This paper focuses on using behavioural traces to predict the quality of social interactions in online games, which involves aspects of social interaction, human-computer interaction, and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper also involves aspects of human-computer interaction (cs.HC), cyberpsychology (cs.CY), natural language processing (cs.CL), and multimedia (cs.MM).
